The paper focuses on the problem of script identification in natural scene images and video frames, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves feature extraction and fusion techniques, which are common in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG) fields. Finally, the paper deals with video frames, which falls under the multimedia (MM) category.
